Aisling C
Mahboula, Kuwait60 contributions
Stop off point
Feb 2020 • Couples
We visited Marble Mountains as part of our journey from Hue to Hoi An. We didn't have high expectations but this place amazed us! It cost 35,000vnd each to enter the Marble Mountains and 15,000vnd each for the use of the lift each way. We chose to get the lift both ways but you could take the lift up and climb down if you had more time. Marble Mountains were beautiful and had so many hidden caves and beautiful ponds. Fantastic views from so high up.
Written February 25, 2020
Tim McIntyre
7 contributions
Don't miss visiting this place!
Stunning caves here with opportunities to get absolutely beautiful pictures. You don't need to do a tour to get to this place. Either take an inexpensive taxi or the 6a bus for 5k. Cost to get in is 40k and another 20k for a separate cave by the entrance. Recommend doing both. Only 15k if you want to take the elevator up. There is still plenty of stairs and steps to do around the complex, so don't exhaust yourself in the beginning and maybe take the elevator. This is a once in a lifetime opportunity to see these caves and well worth it to especially do it inexpensively. Definitely recommend to go.
Written March 5, 2020
Meuok
Bang Sare, Thailand150 contributions
4.0 of 5 bubbles
WORTH A VISIT......
Mar 2020 • Family
I suggest you get yourself here early morning or late afternoon, not like the crazy dogs and Englishman (my lot) out in the midday sun.
We drove (mum dad and 9 year old) here by motorbike from Da Nang, parked up in one of the shops outside and started off with the main cavern complex @ đ20,000.
Caved out, we took the lift @ about đ50,000 each (had I known it (and you want the exercise), you can use the steps for free).
At the top, there are a number of pagodas, gardens and two caves.
Altogether, it's a very nice place.
Take some water with you, as the sales ladies get a touch anxious if you refuse to buy their overpriced drinks.
